  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Calculating average spent with segments</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>A car travels {@d1@} km at {@s1@} km/h, then {@d2@} km at {@s2@} km/h.</p>
<p>Calculate the average speed for the entire {@d1+d2@} km journey.</p>

<p>Average speed = [[input:ans1]] km/h [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p><strong>Step 1: Calculate time for each segment</strong><br>
First segment: Time = \( \frac{@d1@}{@s1@} = {@t1@} \) hours<br>
Second segment: Time = \( \frac{@d2@}{@s2@} = {@t2@} \) hours</p>

<p><strong>Step 2: Calculate total time and total distance</strong><br>
Total distance = {@d1@} + {@d2@} = {@d1+d2@} km<br>
Total time = {@t1@} + {@t2@} = {@t1+t2@} hours</p>

<p><strong>Step 3: Calculate average speed</strong><br>
Average speed = \( \frac{\text{Total distance}}{\text{Total time}} = \frac{@d1+d2@}{@t1+t2@} = {@ta@} \) km/h</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
